.TH HSH 1 "MAY 2026" "Holberton School Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple shell command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
A basic UNIX command line interpreter that executes commands read from standard input.
When running interactively, it prints a "\fC$\fR" prompt before each command.

Input is tokenized using spaces and tabs. Commands are executed by forking a child
process and calling execve(2). If the command contains no slash, hsh searches for
it in the directories listed in the \fIPATH\fR environment variable. If not found, it prints:

.RS
.B $prg_name: 1: $command: not found
.RE

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.I exit
Exits hsh with the stored exit status (initially 0, updated after each command).

.TP
.I env
Prints all environment variables to standard output, one per line.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.I PATH
Colon-separated list of directories searched for commands when no slash is present in the command name. If \fIPATH\fR is unset or empty and no explicit path is given, the command is considered not found.

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on normal startup and EOF (Ctrl+D). After each executed external command, it stores that command's exit status and uses it when exiting later.

.SH SEE ALSO
fork(2), execve(2), wait(2), access(2), getline(3)

